Flux through planes parallel to $y-z=2(1)^{2} \times$ Area

<br/><br/>$$
\begin{aligned}
& =2(1)^{2} \times 2 \times 3 \\\\
& =12 \mathrm{Nm}^{2} / \mathrm{C}
\end{aligned}
$$

<br/><br/>Flux through planes parallel to $x-z=-4(2) \times$ Area

<br/><br/>$$
\begin{aligned}
& =-4(2) \times 1 \times 3 \\\\
& =-24 \mathrm{Nm}^{2} / \mathrm{C}
\end{aligned}
$$

<br/><br/>Flux through planes parallel to $x-y=0$

<br/><br/>$\Rightarrow \phi$ Total $=12-24=-12$

<br/><br/>$\Rightarrow-12=\frac{q_{\mathrm{enc}}}{\varepsilon_{0}} \Rightarrow\left|q_{\mathrm{enc}}\right|=12 \varepsilon_{0}$

<br/><br/>$\Rightarrow n=12$
